dct_title_s: Map shewing the confiscated lands in the Province of Auckland, also the property of the Maori King
dct_description_sm: Relief shown by hachures and spot heights.
At head of title: Enclosure 5 in Sir G. Bowen's despatch no. 49 of the 30th June 1868.
In upper margin: To face page 136. 0.59--Return--New Zealand.
Publisher's no. from its catalog of nineteenth century maps of New Zealand from the British Parliamentary papers: 48.
